    {
        "speciesId": "sliggoo",
        "fastMove": "DRAGON_BREATH",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "BODY_SLAM",
            "DRAGON_PULSE"
        ],
        "weight": 1,
        "editorScore": 90,
        "editorNotes": "From zero to hero, Sliggoo boasts the highest stat product among pure Dragon types. While it's certainly capable, pure Dragon types don't typically see much play over dual-type alternatives like Altaria or Guzzlord. Sliggoo also lacks corebreaking coverage which made Goodra and Shelgon interesting in the past. All in all, it has a few things to prove before it can fully claim hero status."
    },
    {
        "speciesId": "kingdra",
        "fastMove": "DRAGON_BREATH",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "SURF",
            "SWIFT"
        ],
        "weight": 7,
        "editorScore": 91,
        "editorNotes": "Kingdra is on the outside looking in with its new move, Surf. Its typing gives it a neutral profile. It sits ahead of pure Dragon types like Dragonair, but behind the frontrunner, Altaria, whose bulk and coverage are a big step up. Kingdra's niche is its dominating matchups against Fire types, which it double resists."
    },
    {
        "speciesId": "feraligatr",
        "fastMove": "SHADOW_CLAW",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "HYDRO_CANNON",
            "ICE_BEAM"
        ],
        "weight": 14,
        "editorScore": 92,
        "editorNotes": "Feraligatr is a longtime staple thanks to its powerful moveset. Shadow Claw shreds through ever-present Ghost types, and gives it a more neutral profile into other Waters. Preference for Shadow vs non-Shadow is split, currently leaning toward non-Shadow."
    },
    {
        "speciesId": "blastoise",
        "fastMove": "ROLLOUT",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "HYDRO_CANNON",
            "SKULL_BASH"
        ],
        "weight": 7,
        "editorScore": 90,
        "editorNotes": "Blastoise is the bulkiest Hydro Cannon user and can augment this even further with Skull Bash. With an excellent balance of stats, power, and speed, it occupies a small but strong spot in the metagame."
    },
    {
        "speciesId": "dragonair",
        "fastMove": "DRAGON_BREATH",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "AQUA_TAIL",
            "DRAGON_PULSE"
        ],
        "weight": 1,
        "editorScore": 91,
        "editorNotes": "Dragonair is a fast-paced, aggressive pick. Despite its offensive strengths, it falls short of rival Dragons like Altaria, Guzzlord, and Kingdra in terms of bulk and resistances. Because of this, it hasn't seen widespread play in a while, but watch for it in Dragon-centered metas. The Shadow is almost always preferred."
    },
    {
        "speciesId": "dewgong",
        "fastMove": "ICE_SHARD",
        "chargedMoves": [
            "ICY_WIND",
            "DRILL_RUN"
        ],
        "weight": 4,
        "editorScore": 90,
        "editorNotes": "Dewgong has a long competitive history thanks to its bulk and Icy Wind debuffs. It typically underperforms in the sims, where its full game effects aren't well represented. A reworked Drill Run further improves its pacing and damage output, making Dewgong a prospect to watch for."
    },
